{
  "texts": [
    "Their update directions need not form stable subspaces and may conflict substantially with each other.",
    "Consequently, subspace transformations can distort the combined update and push the merged model outside the linearly mode-connected region around the base LLM, increasing the risk of severe degradation.",
    "In contrast, Task Arithmetic makes no subspace assumptions and effectively averages task vectors.",
    "When checkpoints are diverse, this averaging remains close to the base model, yielding modest but consistently positive gains.",
    "This explains why Task Arithmetic succeeds under random sampling, whereas subspace-based methods, though effective in their intended regimes, often underperform or fail in ours."
  ]
}